WRITING.TITLE: Giving my 2 cents
WRITING.TEXT: Yes, I know, yet another feedback post among many other here. However, I think right now is a crucial time for Dauntless and I wanted to share my 2 cents. This will be a longer post so there will be a TL;DR at the bottom: #8203; To begin with, I wanted to express my disappointment in parts of the community. Dauntless is a game shaped by the feedback of our community; Therefore it is important to criticize things you do not like and voice your opinions. However, a few voices in this Subreddit are almost toxic and in no way constructive.This does not help anyone and is rude towards the developers that put so much work into the game. I am aware that this is a small part of the community, but those voices are (sadly) often the loudest. #8203; # My longterm opinion about Dauntelss so far: I have had the pleasure to be part of the amazing journey of Dauntless since the first days of the closed beta. It immediately became one of my favorite games. Since then the game has changed much and most changes were for the better. Phoenix Labs engaged and listened to the community and made changes based on their feedback. This is awesome! There are a few persistent bugs and issues though: The lack of really challenging content in the end game, some bugs have been around for quite some time (e.g Tragic Echo) and do not seem to go away in the near future. I am convinced that Phoenix Labs is working on these issues and I am aware that these things can take time (Sometimes what seems like an easy fix can be a lot of work behind the scenes). Overall, I love the game and the way PL is developing it. #8203; # My opinion on the last few patches: **Scorgestone Hellion:** Nice! A fun, balanced behemoth with good mechanics and which is a worthy rework of the classic Hellion. Less awesome was how overpowered the weapons and molten were; While I understand that there need to be slight balance changes from time to time I find it hard to understand how it was not obvious that molten is Overpowered (especially with the new Weapons and armor). A nerf to molten came 2 weeks later and now it is weaker than EF and Conduit (this is my just my opinion, feel free to change it). It almost seems like PL wanted to get players motivated to go get the new armor and cells and then just nerfed them so they are just average (I am not saying this is the case, I hope and think that PL would not do such a thing, I am just saying it looks like it and could get a few people upset). #8203; **Bugs:** I understand it is a beta and there will be bugs (no such thing as bug free software), but there has to be a limit. It is hard to defend the release of some of the last bugs (e.g. Pangar lantern kills and being stuck on the hunt itself) as they were simply game breaking. These are the kind of bugs that have to be caught before being released. Small bugs are understandable and they often get fixed fast. PL releases a patch almost every week, which is fast, so small bugs I can understand. I do appreciate the quick fix they are deploying right now! #8203; **Hunt pass:** Oh boy! Many people were not happy with this one. First to the plat: I can understand that the pass costs more than you can earn with it (otherwise, PL would likely make a onetime profit for the passes and that is it). The amount of plat that was reduced seems a bit extreme. When you compare the passes, I understand that some people feel baited into buying the Christmas pass only to then get less plat in this one. I doubt that was the intention of PL. Now to the content of the pass: Overall, I think it is acceptable, there are less skins than in the Christmas pass because there are some cool looking emotes. But it feels like there is less than in the Christmas pass when you put in **9** character titles (I mean with elite you get 3 on level one #8230; just why?) also I doubt that anyone is happy about aetherdust. Ace chips and transmog stones are awesome; Those are the consumabels I love to see! I understand however that there cannot be tons of them as they are one of the income sources for PL. If I am not mistaken then in the last pass many people were feeling upset for not getting anything for already completed weeklys, and now again you just get nothing for them? This once again feels like a punishment to active players that are still farming the weeklys every week. And that just feels bad. #8203; **Epic game store:** This one is a hard one. I understand the desire to get Dauntless a bigger audience and that the Epic game store seems like the right place to do just that. Steam takes a 30% cut (if I am not mistaken) which is quite a lot. But a big part of the community does not seem happy with this choice for various reasons. This is a huge decision for PL and will effect Dauntless in a huge way, therefore this decision should not be made lightly. I don #8217;t think that PL really asked the community how they feel about it (I at least don #8217;t recall a survey or anything of the sorts, if I am wrong here then please do tell me!) and that feels bad. I #8217;m not a fan of the Epic Game Store personally for reasons which were mentioned multiple times in various discussions on this Subreddit. The game would greatly benefit from more players so I understand the desire to get Dauntless on a known platform like this, for parts of this community (and many founders) this change is a pretty tough one to swallow. Ultimatley PL will have to make this call and we can either follow or leave the game. This is a crucial decision point for Dauntless and making that call is hard. Whatever they ultimatley choose they will have to accept responsiblity for the outcome. #8203; Still, so far PL has had our backs and i trust them to continue to do so. I think PL have some heavy decisions to make right now and i trust they will make the right ones. I personally am really looking forward to how the awesome journey of dauntless continues! #8203; # TL;DR As a founder of Dauntless i love how PL developed the game so far. The last few patches were a bit of a letdown with some heavy bugs, balancing issures and a battlepass that feels lacking compared to the last one. The Epic Game Store seems to be seriously controversial and we will just have to trust PL to make the right call (whichever one this might be). Still i am looking forward to how Dauntless devolops and what awaits us in the future.

I agree, the cross platform argument is a really strong one. Plus as PL mentioned in their resent post, a lot of the worries that are around (giving data to epic games, worse support than now and so on) are not actually the case. The toughest thing to swallow is the forced name change some people are gonna have.
